  "text": "A noncommutative space is a Morita equivalence class of C * -algebras. In [CITATION_1] it is shown that two UHF-algebras A and A with corresponding invariants s, s ∈ S are Morita equivalent if and only if s ∼ s , and that the additive subgroup Q(s) is the Grothendieck group K 0 (A), so its positive part Q + (s) can be seen as the positive cone of K 0 (A). Hence, we can view the set of equivalence classes",
